    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-07-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1179"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1179">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Léger</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the Republic of Haiti</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Deer Park, Md.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-07-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: I have had the honor to
                    receive your note of the 15th instant by which you are pleased to inform me of
                    the forms which the Department of State desire to see observed by vessels of war
                    of neutral powers entering ports of Cuba and Porto Rico, now in a state of
                    blockade, or in leaving said ports.</p>
                <p>In thanking you for this communication, which I shall not fail to transmit to my
                    Government, I avail with pleasure of this occasion to renew to you, etc.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. N. Léger.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
